P2.2 and P2.3 Test Coverage Implementation
=========================================

Added tests for two packages that had 0% coverage:

1. internal/errors/errors_test.go
   - TestErrorTypes_AreDistinct: Verifies all 9 errors are unique
   - TestErrorWrapping_Is: Tests errors.Is() through wrapping chains
   - TestErrorMessages: Verifies human-readable messages
   - TestWrappedErrorMessages: Tests wrapped error context

2. internal/spending/config_test.go
   - TestDefaultLimits: Verify default values
   - TestLoadLimits_EnvVars: Env var overrides
   - TestLoadLimits_InvalidEnvVarFallsBackToDefault: Graceful handling
   - TestLoadLimits_NoEnvVars: Default behavior
   - TestLoadLimits_PartialEnvVars: Partial overrides
   - TestLoadLimits_ConfigFile: Config file loading
   - TestLoadLimits_EnvOverridesConfigFile: Precedence rules
   - TestLoadLimits_MissingConfigFileNoError: Optional config
   - TestLoadLimits_InvalidConfigFile: Invalid JSON handling
   - TestLimits_JSONSerialization: Round-trip serialization

Key insight: %v vs %w in error wrapping
- %w preserves errors.Is() chain (required for proper error handling)
- %v breaks the chain (test documents this behavior)
